Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Joseph Dudley

[The posting, 23 Oct 2019 Anthrax - Botswana (02): (CH) elephant, susp 20191023.6742740, has the comments: "Preliminary investigations suggest the elephants are dying from anthrax whilst some died from drought effects," and "Due to the severe drought, elephants end up ingesting soil while grazing and get exposed to the anthrax bacteria spore"; which is not to deny the value of Joe's informative comment, and certainly fills an ignorant gap that I had on African elephant feeding. Not unlikely they share a grazing habit of European cattle grazing during a hot dry summer when they are drawn to areas still with some soil moisture and the grass is greener. These saucer areas tend to attract _B. anthracis_ spores as they facilitate spore germination and cell multiplication in the forage root mass. Many thanks to Joe for his valuable comment. - Mod.MHJ

